      "comment": "ASTON MONARCHY (3) pinged the lids last start from an awkward draw and led throughout to score (22.65) at Geelong in a Grade 5 over 400m. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Hard to fault her form and she makes plenty of appeal. DIVA'S ROSE (1) finds it hard to break through. Has been in the minors the last two runs, the latest finishing third (22.64) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning four races. Leading player again. GAPING MARGIN (4) was strong over this course and distance last time despite filling the minors, finishing 1.75 lengths behind Zero Killer in 22.26 and recording a new PB here. Has the ability and can measure up. TICKETS (2) boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip.",
